sequenceDiagram
  participant L as layout()
  participant R as routeElbow() (geometry)
  participant P as perpendicularizeEntry()
  participant F as finishEdges()
  participant E as resolveLabelEdgeCollisions()
  participant S as SVG sink / resvg PNG
  participant T as vnmRuntime twin (runtime.ts)

  Note over L,T: One shared geometry, mirrored byte-for-byte in the runtime twin
  L->>R: route each edge (ports + waypoints)
  R->>P: closing segment ⟂ entered border?
  P-->>R: FR2 — swap last corner if parallel (arrowhead into node)
  R-->>L: routed points + path + labelPos
  L->>F: post-routing passes
  F->>E: label bisected by a run?
  E-->>F: FR3 — slide label off a foreign PARALLEL run (give-up)
  F-->>L: final labelPos
  L->>S: 5-layer emit → static SVG / PNG (theme edge #69728a on light)
  Note over T: interactive HTML export re-derives the same geometry live
  T->>P: perpendicularizeEntry (mirrored)
  T->>E: resolveLabelEdgeCollisions parallel-escape (mirrored)
  Note over S,T: dom-runtime-parity guards toSvgString() == renderSvg
